message.content:
1.1 Classical mechanics: Describes motion of macroscopic objects, predict future and past motions.
1.2 Newtonian mechanics: Based on Newton's Laws, assumes absolute distance, time, and mass.
1.3 Lagrangian mechanics: Formulation based on stationary-action principle by Lagrange.
1.4 Hamiltonian mechanics: Connected to geometry, serves as link between classical and quantum mechanics.
